## Public Member Functions

### adjustForAccess() {#a9c82bb8e10db405d4dd265c150fc52b9}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="AAMDNodes AAMDNodes::adjustForAccess (unsigned AccessSize)">
Create a new AAMDNode for accessing <code>AccessSize</code> bytes of this AAMDNode.

If this AAMDNode has !tbaa.struct and <code>AccessSize</code> matches the size of the field at offset 0, get the TBAA tag describing the accessed field. If such an AAMDNode already embeds !tbaa, the existing one is retrieved. Finally, !tbaa.struct is zeroed out.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/metadata-h/#l00857">857</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/metadata-h">Metadata.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/typebasedaliasanalysis-cpp/#l00827">827</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/typebasedaliasanalysis-cpp">TypeBasedAliasAnalysis.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### concat() {#a17815a975c66fae245b9c87142c3a8b7}

Determine the best <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/aamdnodes">AAMDNodes</a> after concatenating two different locations together.

Different from <code>merge</code>, where different locations should overlap each other, <code>concat</code> puts non-overlapping locations together.
